WEBVTT

00:18.685 --> 00:21.787
(male announcer)
previously on <i>gracepoint...</i>

00:21.789 --> 00:23.222
(emmett)
they're panicking,
starting to show themselves.

00:23.224 --> 00:24.456
<i>That's exactly what we want.</i>

00:24.458 --> 00:25.724
(ellie)
our burned boat,

00:25.726 --> 00:28.293
It belonged
to my brother-in-law.

00:28.295 --> 00:29.528
Who knew it was there?

00:29.530 --> 00:31.463
I don't want
anything to do with you.

00:31.465 --> 00:33.732
I know men who'd rape you.

00:33.734 --> 00:34.733
You have any kids?
Daughter.

00:34.735 --> 00:36.402
17, lives with her mother.

00:36.404 --> 00:38.203
This is dad.
Please try me.

00:38.205 --> 00:39.571
You're the detective's kid.

00:39.573 --> 00:41.373
Come and knock on my door
sometime.

00:41.375 --> 00:42.574
Found this.

00:42.576 --> 00:43.642
That's danny's phone.

00:43.644 --> 00:44.877
Forensics get anything
off it?

00:44.879 --> 00:47.246
No data, no texts,
no call log.

00:47.248 --> 00:49.815
I know about you
and gemma fisher.

00:49.817 --> 00:51.250
I saw him with someone.

00:51.252 --> 00:52.918
With who?
Backpacker.

00:52.920 --> 00:54.753
Lars pierson.

00:54.755 --> 00:57.156
His cell number was found
in the lining of danny's jacket.

00:57.158 --> 00:58.891
Pointing the finger
at an innocent man.

00:58.893 --> 01:00.225
That's not the version
we submitted.

01:00.227 --> 01:02.061
What are you doing
to protect jack reinhold?

01:02.063 --> 01:04.063
You're asking for help,
but you won't talk to us.

01:04.065 --> 01:06.331
Vince is rounding up
a lynch mob.

01:40.633 --> 01:43.102
[knocking at the door]

01:44.571 --> 01:48.740
They're scum,
the bunch of 'em.

01:48.742 --> 01:50.609
They hounded
that poor man to death,

01:50.611 --> 01:55.214
And now they're
playing innocent.

01:55.216 --> 01:58.550
If you're coming,
you'll need a black one.

02:00.286 --> 02:03.789
County supervisor's
cutting our budget.

02:03.791 --> 02:05.257
What?

02:05.259 --> 02:06.892
Starting next week.

02:06.894 --> 02:09.261
He's pulling staff support,
forensic requests.

02:09.263 --> 02:10.796
He can't do that.

02:10.798 --> 02:12.898
That's what happens
when a case drags on.

02:12.900 --> 02:15.801
Bosses lose confidence,
panic about accounting.

02:15.803 --> 02:19.071
But we can't pull back.
Pierson's still out there.

02:19.073 --> 02:21.940
C.S.I.'s combing the property
out at the harvey ridge hut.

02:21.942 --> 02:23.842
We're still looking over--
get it done this week.

02:23.844 --> 02:25.811
Drag everyone in.

02:25.813 --> 02:29.348
Rack up overtime
before he pulls the rug out.

02:29.350 --> 02:31.150
Know what might help?

02:31.152 --> 02:34.920
Nailing whoever vandalized
jack reinhold's shop.

02:34.922 --> 02:36.955
Might win us brownie points.

02:36.957 --> 02:40.859
You know, you don't
have to come to the funeral.

02:40.861 --> 02:43.762
'cause of this?

02:43.764 --> 02:46.031
Screw 'em.

02:46.033 --> 02:49.268
You think they're right?
Worst cop in california?

02:50.637 --> 02:53.272
Maybe top ten.

02:55.642 --> 02:59.044
Danny's killer could
easily be there.

02:59.046 --> 03:00.712
With another death
on their conscience,

03:00.714 --> 03:03.282
Let's see who's
looking worried.

03:03.284 --> 03:05.951
Doesn't seem right.
Burying jack,

03:05.953 --> 03:08.520
And they still won't let us
have danny's body.

03:08.522 --> 03:10.556
Well, they have to find
the killer first.

03:10.558 --> 03:13.091
Can we not do this
right now?

03:17.797 --> 03:20.732
You know,
I-I've been thinking,

03:20.734 --> 03:23.535
Maybe I should
start working again.

03:23.537 --> 03:25.404
When?

03:25.406 --> 03:28.040
I don't know.
Next week maybe.

03:28.042 --> 03:30.042
I mean, vince can't carry
the business forever,

03:30.044 --> 03:31.476
And we need the money.

03:32.812 --> 03:34.213
If you want me to stay home,
I can--

03:34.215 --> 03:35.647
No, no, no, no.
You are probably right.

03:35.649 --> 03:37.049
We need the money.

03:37.051 --> 03:40.852
I will find something
to do here alone.

03:40.854 --> 03:42.354
You could go back
to the visitor's center.

03:42.356 --> 03:43.855
[sighs]

03:43.857 --> 03:45.591
Get direction
from the dead boy's mom--

03:45.593 --> 03:46.592
That'll pack 'em into town.
I'll be fine.

03:46.594 --> 03:47.593
[footsteps approaching]

03:47.595 --> 03:48.694
Nope, no way.

03:48.696 --> 03:50.696
I said, "black."

03:50.698 --> 03:51.930
I didn't even like him.

03:51.932 --> 03:53.665
Change.

03:53.667 --> 03:55.167
[sighs]

